  one reading.

  *On the Turba Philosophorum:* The First through Third Dictums establish the unity
  and primacy of water as the origin of all things. This anticipates Year Two's
  water work and plants the seed of the year-long theme without drawing explicit
  attention to it. The student need not understand the Turba fully — the first
  exposure is for imprinting, not comprehension.
